Problem:
class WeatherSimulator {
  private boolean isRaining;
  private int temperature;
  public WeatherSimulator(int temperature, boolean isRaining) {
    this.temperature = temperature;
    this.isRaining = isRaining;
  }
  public void adjustWeather(int newTemp) {
    if (newTemp < 0) {
        this.isRaining = false;
    }
    this.temperature = newTemp;
  }
  public boolean checkUmbrellaNeed() {
    return isRaining && temperature <= 20;
  }
}",

If a person needs an umbrella, was the temperature necessarily below 20 degrees?
